cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper involves training a model to play a video game using reinforcement learning algorithms, specifically Deep Q-Network and Asynchronous Advantage Actor Critic. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of raw game images suggests computer vision (cs.CV) may be relevant. The game itself is a graphically simple 2D game, which could fall under computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning suggests neural networks (cs.NE) may also be relevant.
